  "notes": "Calabrian. Southern Italo-Romance of Calabria. Internally diverse: N. Calabria patterns with the Neapolitan dialect continuum, S. Calabria with Sicilian. Key features: (1) Vowel reduction to […Щ]. (2) Metaphony. (3) Retroflex consonants in S. Calabria (-LL-вЖТ[…ЦЋР], TRвЖТ[ И…љ]). (4) Strong Greek substrate influence. Griko (Italo-Greek) still spoken in pockets (Fanciullo 2015, Rohlfs 1966).",
